<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:39:25 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>侵蚀美德：人工智能训练人们期待即时答案——这对耐心来说是个坏消息</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/eroding-a-virtue-ai-trains-people-to-expect-instant-answers-and-thats-bad-news-for-patience</link><description>研究人员认为，耐心是一种美德，它与幸福的许多方面息息相关。但它也需要一些练习和训练，并且可能会被即时、轻松的满足感所破坏。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/eroding-a-virtue-ai-trains-people-to-expect-instant-answers-and-thats-bad-news-for-patience.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:39:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/eroding-a-virtue-ai-trains-people-to-expect-instant-answers-and-thats-bad-news-for-patience</guid></item><item><title>捕获超冷氢气的前体</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/trapping-a-precursor-to-ultracold-hydrogen</link><description>研究人员利用激光冷却和捕获来分离一氢化钙，这是生产超冷原子氢的关键一步。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/trapping-a-precursor-to-ultracold-hydrogen2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:24:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/trapping-a-precursor-to-ultracold-hydrogen</guid></item><item><title>振动使电子团结起来</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/vibrations-make-electrons-team-up</link><description>原子尺度的测量表明，振动激发可以导致电子成束移动。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/vibrations-make-electrons-team-up2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 15:09:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/vibrations-make-electrons-team-up</guid></item><item><title>新分析反驳宇宙加速减速的说法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/cosmic-acceleration-holds-up-as-new-analysis-rebuts-slowdown-claim</link><description>一个国际天体物理学家团队表示，尽管最近的说法表明事实并非如此，但我们的宇宙仍在加速膨胀。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cosmic-acceleration-holds-up-as-new-analysis-rebuts-slowdown-claim.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 14:54:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/cosmic-acceleration-holds-up-as-new-analysis-rebuts-slowdown-claim</guid></item><item><title>银纳米颗粒为精确 DNA 切割和连接铺平了道路</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/silver-nanoparticles-pave-the-way-for-precise-dna-cutting-and-joining</link><description>DNA 由长链组成，是生物体的蓝图。在基因工程中，科学家在特定位点切割 DNA，并将所得片段与其他 DNA 序列连接起来，从而实现先进作物育种、遗传疾病治疗以及用于药物发现的动物模型生成等应用。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/silver-nanoparticles-pave-the-way-for-precise-dna-cutting-and-joining.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 14:39:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/silver-nanoparticles-pave-the-way-for-precise-dna-cutting-and-joining</guid></item><item><title>自 2000 年以来，每年的全球移民数量几乎增加了两倍，重塑了人们的迁徙地点和方式</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/annual-global-migration-has-nearly-tripled-since-2000-reshaping-where-and-how-people-move</link><description>全球移民数量已从 2000 年的每年约 1300 万人急剧增加到 2023 年的每年约 3500 万人。这是根据人类移民的新数据集得出的&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/annual-global-migration-has-nearly-tripled-since-2000-reshaping-where-and-how-people-move2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 14:24:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/annual-global-migration-has-nearly-tripled-since-2000-reshaping-where-and-how-people-move</guid></item><item><title>俄罗斯卫星与多个国家的神秘 GPS 中断有关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/russian-satellites-linked-to-mysterious-gps-disruptions-across-several-countries</link><description>自 2019 年以来，欧洲、格陵兰岛和加拿大的 GPS 信号出现了突然、大范围信号中断的情况。这些导致飞机和船舶安全行驶所依赖的导航系统中断和性能下降。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/russian-satellites-linked-to-mysterious-gps-disruptions-across-several-countries2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 14:09:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/russian-satellites-linked-to-mysterious-gps-disruptions-across-several-countries</guid></item><item><title>人工智能有助于揭示隐藏在堆叠原子片中的大规模量子效应</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ai-helps-reveal-large-scale-quantum-effects-hidden-in-stacked-atomic-sheets</link><description>量子材料是一类具有特殊性质的奇异材料，受量子力学而非经典物理学控制。这些特性——如超导性、纠缠和不寻常的磁性——通常起源于晶体内部原子的微小重复模式，但通过巧妙的工程，可以在更人性化的尺度上观察和控制它们。量子材料正在帮助推动快速发展的量子计算领域，并可能进入下一代节能电子产品。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ai-helps-reveal-large-scale-quantum-effects-hidden-in-stacked-atomic-sheets.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 13:54:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/ai-helps-reveal-large-scale-quantum-effects-hidden-in-stacked-atomic-sheets</guid></item><item><title>新研究发现人们并不像我们想象的那样不诚实</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/people-are-not-as-dishonest-as-we-expect-them-to-be-finds-new-study</link><description>根据皮尤研究中心的一份报告，美国人之间的信任程度比几十年前要低。社会信任很大程度上取决于个人在世界各地的经历，以及人们对他人在日常生活中可能诚实或不诚实行为的坚信程度。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/people-are-not-as-dishonest-as-we-expect-them-to-be-finds-new-study2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 13:39:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/people-are-not-as-dishonest-as-we-expect-them-to-be-finds-new-study</guid></item><item><title>细胞有一条秘密的电源线：细胞核如何从线粒体获得自己的私人能量供应</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/cells-have-a-secret-power-line-how-the-nucleus-gets-its-own-private-energy-supply-from-mitochondria</link><description>几十年来，生物学家一直认为细胞的能量只是扩散到需要的地方。事实证明，最重要的目的地有一条私人送货线路。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/cells-have-a-secret-power-line-how-the-nucleus-gets-its-own-private-energy-supply-from-mitochondria2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jun 2026 13:24:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/06/cells-have-a-secret-power-line-how-the-nucleus-gets-its-own-private-energy-supply-from-mitochondria</guid></item></channel></rss>